    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Synchronizer Assembly (13-Speed Models)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spread the countershaft assemblies and pull the synchronizer assembly from the splines of
                the range mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018a4">Figure 104</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018a4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018a4" filename="../figg13/G13018a4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 104. Pull Synchronizer Assembly From Splines of Range Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To spread countershafts far enough to remove the synchronizer on RTO and RTOO models, move the
                        splitter clutch to the forward position.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
